The dynamic wasn't necessarily a healthy one; surely, it's better to negotiate without being in constant crisis mode. But Congress has become so familiar with the crisis that the dire nature of the situation doesn't even move them anymore. They dangerously moved the needle a couple of years ago, balking at raising the debt ceiling (causing the lowering of the nations' credit rating as a result).
